Key Findings:
Churn Rate: Currently at 27%.
Contract Insights: Month-to-month contracts see a high churn rate of 45%, whereas one-year and two-year contracts fare much better with churn rates of 11% and 3%, respectively.
Payment Method Impact: Electronic check users have a higher churn rate, highlighting a need for encouraging more stable payment options.
Support Tickets: A higher number of technical support tickets correlate with increased churn, suggesting a need for improved technical support.
Recommendations:
Promote long-term contracts to customers to decrease churn rates.
Encourage customers to switch from electronic checks to more reliable payment methods.
Enhance technical support services to address and reduce frequent issues.
Project Highlights:
Developed a Power BI dashboard providing comprehensive insights.
Used advanced data analysis to drive actionable recommendations.
